Subject Lin e: 2025 RHOA  B o ard & Our Prio rities 
 
Target Release D ate: 9/22/2025 
 
Hello Runnymeade neighbors, 
 
Thank you to everyone who participated in our recent B oard of D irectors election during the 
A nnual Meeting this past July. A t the monthly A ugust meeting, officer positions were assigned, 
and we’re excited to introduce your new HOA  B oard of D irectors: 
  ●  Presiden t, Jess Kratz 
●  Vice Presiden t, B o b Jarecke: A  Runnymeade homeowner since 1991, and, as a retired 
U.S. A ir Force officer, he now has more time to give back to our community. Over the 
years, he’s seen our neighborhood evolve, and wants to help keep it safe, welcoming, 
and well cared for, whether that’s improving landscaping, fixing streetlights, or reducing 
litter.  
●  Secretary, Mo n ica B rito : Moved to Runnymeade in 2024 with her husband and our 
puppy, Paddington. A s secretary, she wants to keep communication open so residents 
feel informed and connected with the board. B y day, shes a communicator helping 
federal agencies communicate initiatives, and by night you’ll catch her watching the Real 
Housewives franchises. 
●  Treasurer, C aitlin  D arden n e: Moved to Runnymeade in 2022 with her husband and has 
since welcomed 2 beautiful boys to her family. She joined the B oard a year later with an 
excitement to help the community to prosper, enhance the family-friendly nature of the 
neighborhood, through things like expanded social events, and is looking forward to 
finding ways to make the HOA’s finances work better for the community. 
●  Member-at-Large, Jan e Yo un g: Has lived in Runnymeade since 2018 and has served 
on the board as a member-at-large for the last 2+ years. She volunteered to be on the 
board because she cares about the community! 
 
Our Missio n : 
A s your B oard, our mission is to responsibly manage the community’s business activities and 
finances to ensure our community remains a pleasant, cooperative, and safe place to live. This 
year, we’ll be focusing: 
  ●  Improving upkeep of common areas and landscaping 
●  Ensuring streetlights and other community infrastructure are in good working order 
●  Reducing litter and keeping our neighborhood clean 
●  Supporting open communication with residents 
 
Ho w Yo u C an  Get In vo lved! 
We’re always looking for volunteers to help make Runnymeade even better. If you’re passionate 
about a community initiative or have an idea you’d like to champion, reach out to the B oard 
(email below), we would love to work with you to form a subcommittee!  

 
Need to  get in  to uch? 
A s a reminder, you can always reach the B oard through the following: 
  ●  Visit: https://portal.keymontcm.com/home_v2/Login 
●  Email the B oard: runnymeadehoa@googlegroups.com  
●  C ontact our Property Manager: C orey B lackston at cblackston@keymontcm.com and 
703-752-8302 x745 
 
Pro p erty Man agemen t C o mp an y Rebran d:  
A s a reminder, Gates Hudson has transitioned to Keymont C ommunity Management, but there 
will be no interruption in service for residents. The B oard will share any updates as they become 
available. 
 
Jo in  us fo r To mo rro w’s HOA  Meetin g! 
Join us on Tuesday, September 23 at 7:00 PM via Zoom: 
https://us06web.zoom.us/j/82938022635?pwd=7w1lBPapPwUpY3SZLQ8pludFV3rZtz.1 
 
We appreciate your continued engagement and look forward to working together to keep 
Runnymeade a great place to live! 
 
Sincerely, 
Your Runnymeade HOA  B oard of D irectors

Dear Wesley G Scholl & Yan Yuan, 

Keymont Community Management (KCM) congratulates you on the purchase of your new home and welcomes 
you to your new community, Runnymeade Homeowners Association. 

WHO WE ARE & WHAT WE DO:  KCM is the Association’s managing agent. We are a local premier full-service 
association  management  company  specializing  in  all  types  of  association  management  throughout  the 
Washington, DC Metropolitan area. Please visit our website to learn more about us: keymontcm.com. 

The operation and management of your Association is controlled by your Association’s governing documents 
with direction provided by an elected Board of Directors. A KCM Manager meets regularly with your Board of 
Directors  to  review  and  report  on  the  quality  of  vendor  services,  maintenance  issues,  owner  compliance,  and 
overall operations of your Association.  In short, we work hard to help keep everything running smoothly.

WHERE/HOW TO FIND INFORMATION ABOUT YOUR ASSOCIATION & YOUR ACCOUNT: 

1. Create your account in the Homeowner Portal: 

Your association’s homeowner portal is where you will check your account balance, make online payments, 
see your association’s documents, submit requests, view community calendars, and receive important 
information about your community. 

To create your account, go to https://home.keymontcm.com and click on the 'Sign Up' link. 
Use the following information to create your account:

Account Number: 83RH84437
Portal Registration Key: 34DF60A623C8

  Our portal is SOC-2 and PCI Level 1 compliant, role and password protected, and 128-bit encrypted.

2. Set up your association assessment payments:
To submit a one-time payment or set up a recurring payment: 
1. Log in to your account https://home.keymontcm.com
2. Navigate to the Payments page to review all options
3. Click on the ‘Make a Payment’ button. 
4. Set up optional automated text reminders by going to ‘My Profile’ then ‘Preferences’.

                        

                           
 3020 Hamaker Court  Suite 300  Fairfax, Virginia  22031  KeymontCM.com  (703) 752-8300

We offer the following payment options:  
• Automatic Draft Payment (ACH) • One-Time and Recurring eCheck • Credit Card 

Please review all options. Also look for a coupon book/statement in the mail in the near future. 

3. Update your contact information

It is essential we have current contact information at all times, so you are informed of important association-
related business. When/if your email, mailing address, phone number or other contact information changes, 
please make these updates in the portal on the ‘My Profile’ page. You can also elect to hide or display your 
contact information in the online community directory.

If you don’t find the information you need on the portal, we can be reached at 
communications@keymontcm.com or (703) 752-8300 during regular business hours (8:30 a.m. – 5:00 p.m. 
Monday-Thursday and 8:30 a.m. – 2:00 p.m. Friday), and we will be happy to assist. After-hours emergency 
calls should be directed to (888) 660-7132.

Congratulations on the purchase of your new property, and welcome to the community!

Sent on behalf of Runnymeade Homeowners Association
This Community is Professionally Managed by:
Keymont Community Management
